<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1936-07-27T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1936-07-27T00:00:00-05:00" n="613" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d613">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">852.00/2291: Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Spain</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Bowers</hi></persName>), <hi rend="italic">Then in France, to the <gloss type="to">Secretary
                                        of State</gloss></hi></head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">St.
                                            Jean de Luz</hi></placeName> [<date ana="#date_undated-inferred-from-document-content-and-sibling-dates" calendar="gregorian" when="1936-07-27">undated</date>.]<lb/>[Received July 27, 1936—3:45
                                    p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>Since unable to communicate have proceeded St. Jean de Luz, France,
                                Golf Hotel, in order to confer with colleagues there. Shall return
                                Fuenterrabia tomorrow and spend part time in each. Send cables mail
                                St. Jean. Request <hi rend="italic">Cayuga</hi> be kept my sole
                                disposition. If necessary transship cadets other ship at St.
                                Jean.</p>
                            <closer><signed><hi rend="smallcaps">Bowers</hi></signed></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>